[thinking] I'm noticing a potential issue with cglib's createClass that uses callback types but doesn’t have callbacks, with classOnly set to true. It seems like it could generate a class, but the native image might struggle because it can't define a runtime class and could catch an unsupported Error. I wonder if the dynamic access reports for "nativeTestCompile" could relate to instrumentation occurring during the test run. I guess I need to consider test generation and static callbacks more closely.
[thinking] 
