lback types but doesn’t have callbacks, with classOnly set to true. It seems like it could generate a class, but the native image might struggle because it can't define a runtime class and could catch an unsupported Error. I wonder if the dynamic access reports for \\\"nativeTestCompile\\\" could relate to instrumentation occurring during the test run. I guess I need to consider test generation and static callbacks more closely.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_f8PheMmuKVTGf1TOLnDSsRNh|fc_0274a956a114fa4d016a030b1720ec8196a7f8cb119c09badb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.sonatype.sisu.inject/cglib/2.2.1-v20090111/main/extracted/net/sf/cglib/proxy/FixedValue.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6893, "output": 1450, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32407, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778584321453, "responseId": "resp_0274a956a114fa4d016a030b0216ec81968cf73dcdfe077462"}}
