ck types but doesn’t have callbacks, with classOnly set to true. It seems like it could generate a class, but the native image might struggle because it can't define a runtime class and could catch an unsupported Error. I wonder if the dynamic access reports for \\\"nativeTestCompile\\\" could relate to instrumentation occurring during the test run. I guess I need to consider test generation and static callbacks more closely.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_f8PheMmuKVTGf1TOLnDSsRNh|fc_0274a956a114fa4d016a030b1720ec8196a7f8cb119c09badb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.sonatype.sisu.inject/cglib/2.2.1-v20090111/main/extracted/net/sf/cglib/proxy/FixedValue.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6893, "output": 1450, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32407, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778584321453, "responseId": "resp_0274a956a114fa4d016a030b0216ec81968cf73dcdfe077462"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_f8PheMmuKVTGf1TOLnDSsRNh|fc_0274a956a114fa4d016a030b1720ec8196a7f8cb119c09badb", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright 2003 The Apache Software Foundation\n *\n *  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n *  Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage net.sf.cglib.proxy;\n\n/**\n * {@link Enhancer} callback that simply returns the value to return\n * from the proxied method. No information about what method\n * is being called is available to the callback, and the type of\n * the returned object must be compatible with the return type of\n * the proxied method. This makes this callback primarily useful\n * for forcing a particular method (through the use of a {@link CallbackFilter}\n * to return a fixed value with little overhead.\n */\npublic interface FixedValue extends Callback {\n    /**\n     * Return the object which the original method invocation should\n     * return. This method is called for <b>every</b> method invocation.\n     * @return an object matching the type of the return value for every\n     * method this callback is mapped to\n     */\n    Object loadObject() throws Exception;\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778584343673}]}
